1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 { Avoiding the Slav Exchange } (2... c6 3. cxd5 cxd5) 3. Nf3 c6 4. Qc2 (4. Qb3 Nf6 5. g3 (5. Bg5 Nbd7 6. Nc3 h6!? 7. Bf4 (7. Bh4 dxc4 8. Qxc4 a6! { preparing b5 and Bb7 } 9. e3 c5 10. Qa4 Rb8!) 7... a5! 8. e3 a4 9. Qc2 a3 $36 { 1/2 Indjic,A (2605)-Shevchenko,K (2652) EU-ch 22nd Terme Catez 2022 (6) }) (5. Nc3 dxc4 6. Qxc4 b5 7. Qd3 (7. Qb3 a6 8. Bg5 Nbd7 9. e4 (9. e3 c5 10. Be2 Bb7 { Black has achieved an ideal set-up }) 9... c5! 10. d5 (10. Be2) 10... c4 { 1/2 Kortschnoj,V (2630)-Novikov,I (2575) Pamplona 9091 1st 1990 } 11. Qc2 Be7 12. Rd1 Qc7 $15) 7... Bb7 8. e4 (8. Bg5 Nbd7 9. e4 (9. e3 { black gets very comfortable position after playing a6,c5 } 9... a6 10. Be2 c5 11. O-O Be7 12. dxc5 Nxc5 13. Qxd8+ Rxd8 14. Rac1 O-O 15. Nd4 Rc8 { 0-1 Andersson,U (2640)-Beliavsky,A (2710) EU-Cup 13th Group4 Parnu 1997 (1) with much easier play for black }) (9. a3 a6 10. e4 c5 11. d5 c4 12. Qc2 Qc7 (12... Be7! 13. Rd1 Nxd5!!) 13. dxe6 fxe6 $17 { 1/2 Kortschnoj,V (2623)-Grischuk,A (2717) Odessa Pivdenny Bank rapid 2007 (4) Grischuk wasn't able to convert the advantage against Kortschnoj }) 9... b4 10. Na4 Qa5 11. b3 c5 12. Bxf6 (12. d5!? exd5 13. exd5 Bd6 14. Qe2+ Kf8 15. Qc2 Re8+ $40 { 1-0 Bu,X (2673)-Gasanov,E (2536) Moscow op-A 2010 (2) }) 12... gxf6 13. Be2 (13. d5?! O-O-O! 14. Be2 f5 15. exf5 Nb6 16. Nxb6+ Qxb6 17. O-O Rxd5 18. Qe3 Rxf5 $17 { Black has a powerful attack on the kingside and white doesn't have enough compensation for the pawn } 19. Ne5 Rg8 20. g3 Bg7 { 0-1 Kortschnoj,V (2659)-Ivanchuk,V (2709) Leonid Stein Memorial Lvov 2000 (4) }) 13... cxd4 14. Qxd4 Rd8 15. O-O Be7 16. Rac1 Nb6 17. Qe3 Nxa4 18. bxa4 O-O! { with better chances for black } (18... Qxa4? 19. Nd4! $18)) (8. a3 a6 9. e4 (9. b4 a5! $17) 9... c5! 10. e5 (10. dxc5 Bxc5) 10... c4! { providing the d5 for the knight } 11. Qc2 Nd5 12. Be2 Nc6 13. O-O Na5! $17) (8. g3 c5! { rare move, it was played only once by GM Lintchevski D. } 9. Qxb5+ (9. Nxb5 { the d4 pawn falls } 9... a6 10. Na3 cxd4 11. Bg2 e5) (9. Bg2 b4 10. Nb1 (10. Na4 Be4 11. Qb3 cxd4 $15) 10... Nbd7 11. O-O Rc8 12. Nbd2 a5 13. b3 Be7 14. Bb2 O-O 15. Rac1 a4! 16. bxa4 Nb6 17. a5 Na4 $36) 9... Bc6 10. Qc4 cxd4 11. Nb1 Qd5? (11... Nbd7 12. Qxc6 Rc8 $19) 12. Qxd5 Bxd5 13. Bg2 Nc6 14. O-O e5 15. e3 Bc5 16. exd4 Nxd4 17. Nxd4 Bxd4 18. Nd2 Rd8 19. Bxd5 Rxd5 20. Rb1 O-O 21. b3 Rc8 22. Nc4 Ne4 23. Bb2 f6 24. Kg2 Rcd8 25. Rfe1 Nc5 26. Re2 Bxb2 27. Rbxb2 Nd3 28. Rbc2 Nb4 29. Rc3 Rd3 30. Rc1 Rd1 31. Rxd1 Rxd1 32. a3 Nc6 33. Rd2 Rxd2 34. Nxd2 Nd4 35. b4 Kf7 36. Nb1 Ke6 37. Nc3 Kd6 38. f4 exf4 39. gxf4 Kc6 40. a4 Nc2 41. b5+ Kb6 42. Kf3 f5 43. Ke2 Nd4+ 44. Kd3 Kc5 45. h4 g6 46. Kd2 Kc4 47. Na2 Nf3+ 48. Ke3 Nd4 49. Nc1 Nc2+ 50. Kd2 Nb4 51. Ne2 Nd5 52. h5 gxh5 53. Ng3 h4 54. Nxf5 h3 55. Ng3 Nxf4 56. Ke3 Ne6 57. Kf2 Kb4 58. Nf5 Kxa4 59. Nd6 Nc7 60. Kg3 Nxb5 61. Nf5 Kb3 { 0-1 Tunik,G (2430)-Lintchevski,D (2546) Nezhmetdinov Memorial 36th Kazan 2014 (7) }) 8... b4 9. Na4 Qa5 10. b3 c5 11. Ne5 (11. e5 Ba6 12. Qc2 Bxf1 13. Rxf1 Nd5 14. dxc5 Nd7 15. Be3 Rc8 16. O-O-O Bxc5 $19 { 0-1 So,W (2761)-Kramnik,V (2753) Titled Tuesday intern op 28th Mar Early Chess.com INT blitz 2023 (10) White king is exposed and very vulnerable }) (11. Qb5+ Qxb5 12. Bxb5+ Bc6 13. Bxc6+ Nxc6 14. dxc5 Nxe4 { pawn on c5 is weak }) 11... cxd4! (11... Nbd7?! 12. Qb5 Qc7 13. Bf4 a6 $13 { 0-1 Lazavik,D (2578)-So,W (2752) Julius Baer GenCup D2 W Chess.com INT rapid 2024 (5.2) }) 12. Qb5+ Qxb5 13. Bxb5+ Nfd7 14. Bb2 f6 15. Nxd7 Nxd7 16. Bxd4 Bxe4 17. O-O Bd6 18. Rfe1 Bd5) 5... dxc4 6. Qxc4 b5 { transposes to 4.Qc2 }) (4. Nbd2 Nf6 5. g3 (5. e3 Be7 (5... Nbd7!? 6. Bd3 Bd6 7. O-O O-O 8. e4 e5! 9. cxd5 cxd5 10. exd5 exd4 11. Ne4 Nxe4 12. Bxe4 Nf6 13. Bg5 (13. Qxd4 Nxe4 14. Qxe4 Re8 15. Qd4 Bf5 16. Bg5 Qa5 17. Bd2 Qb6 18. Bc3 Qxd4 19. Nxd4 Bd7 20. Rfe1 f6 21. Ne6 Kf7 { 1/2 Nakamura,H (2749)-Duda,J (2731) Saint Louis Champions Showdown blitz 2019 (2.2) Black has a pair of bishops and a full compensation for the pawn }) 13... Be7 14. Bxf6 Bxf6 15. Nxd4 Qb6 $44) 6. Bd3 O-O 7. O-O Nbd7 8. e4 dxe4 9. Nxe4 c5! { Rubinstein variaton of French defence } 10. Nxc5 Nxc5 11. dxc5 Bxc5 12. Bg5 h6 13. Bh4 b6 14. Qe2 Bb7 15. Rad1 Qc7 16. Bxf6 gxf6 17. Be4 (17. Nh4) 17... Rfd8 $36) (5. Qc2 Be7 6. g3 O-O 7. Bg2 b6 8. O-O c5!) 5... Be7 (5... c5!? { Black wants to take the game into Tarrasch defence } 6. cxd5 exd5 7. Bg2 Nc6 8. O-O h6 9. Re1 cxd4 10. Nb3 Bd6 11. Nbxd4 O-O 12. b3 Re8 13. Bb2 Bb4 (13... Ne4 { With a great play }) 14. Rf1 Nxd4 15. Qxd4 Ba5 16. Qd3 Bb6 17. Rad1 Be6 18. Nd4 Bg4 19. Rfe1 Rc8 20. h3 Bh5 21. g4 Bg6 22. Nf5 h5 23. Bf3 hxg4 24. hxg4 Ne4? { 0-1 Deac,B (2702)-Carlsen,M (2839) Titled Tuesday intern op 12th Sep Late Chess.com INT blitz 2023 (8) } (24... Nxg4!! 25. Bxg4 Qg5 $19)) 6. Bg2 O-O 7. O-O { Transferred to Catalan game } 7... b6 8. Qc2 c5 9. dxc5 bxc5 10. b3 Nc6 11. Bb2 Bb7 12. Ne5 Nb4 13. Qb1 a5! 14. cxd5 exd5 15. a3 Nc6 16. Nxc6 Bxc6 { 1/2 Mendonca,L (2603)-Maghsoodloo,P (2734) Sharjah Masters 6th 2023 (7) }) 4... Nf6 5. g3 (5. Bg5 dxc4 6. Qxc4 b5 7. Qc2 Bb7 8. e3 (8. e4!? { Always has to be under consideration } 8... Nbd7 9. Nbd2 (9. e5 h6!) 9... a6 10. a4 h6 11. Bxf6 Nxf6 12. Bd3 Bb4 13. O-O O-O 14. e5 Nd7 15. Ne4 bxa4 16. Rxa4 c5 $36) (8. Nbd2 Nbd7 9. e4 a6) 8... Nbd7 9. Nbd2 (9. Bd3 a6 10. a4 Bb4+!? { Quiet unusual, but the bishop occupies the b4 square } 11. Nc3 c5 12. axb5 c4! 13. Be2 (13. Bxc4 axb5 14. Ba2 Ra5) 13... axb5 14. O-O Bxc3 15. Qxc3 Ne4) 9... a6 10. a4 Rc8 11. Be2 Be7 12. O-O O-O 13. Qb3 Nb6 14. Bxf6 gxf6 15. Ne4 Qd5?! { 0-1 Iljushin,A (2551)-Zhigalko,S (2668) Moscow op-A 2010 (4) } (15... Nxa4! 16. Rxa4 Qd5 17. Qxd5 exd5 18. Nxf6+ Bxf6 19. Ra2 $13)) (5. Bf4!? dxc4 6. Qxc4 b5 7. Qc2 Bb7 8. e4 Nbd7 9. Nbd2 a6 10. a4 Bb4 11. Bd3 c5 12. axb5 axb5 13. O-O c4 14. Be2 Rc8 15. d5 Qb6 16. dxe6 fxe6 17. e5 Nd5 { 0-1 Ponomariov,R (2754)-Nakamura,H (2774) Saint Louis m1 rap rapid 2011 (3) }) 5... dxc4 6. Qxc4 b5 7. Qc2 (7. Qd3!? { Keeping the pressure on the b5 pawn } 7... Bb7 8. Bg2 Nbd7 9. O-O a6! 10. a4 c5 11. axb5 Be4 12. Qb3 Bd5 13. Qc2 axb5 14. Rxa8 Qxa8 15. Nc3 Bc6 16. dxc5 Bxc5 17. Bg5 (17. Ne1 Bxg2 18. Nxg2 b4 19. Na4 Be7 20. Bg5 (20. Be3 Nd5 21. Rc1 O-O 22. Qc6 Qxc6 23. Rxc6 Ra8 24. b3 Bf6 25. Bd2 { 1/2 Sidorika,V (2308)-Pavlov,S (2480) Kiev Spring Rapid op 2021 (4) }) 20... O-O 21. Rc1 h6 22. Bxf6 Bxf6 23. Qc6 Qa7 24. b3 Bd4 25. e3 Ne5 26. Qe4 f5! 27. Qc2 Nf3+ 28. Kh1 Bc3 29. Nxc3 bxc3 30. Qxc3 Qa2 31. Qc2 Qxc2 32. Rxc2 g5 33. Rc1 Rb8) 17... O-O 18. Bxf6 Nxf6 19. Nxb5 Bxf2+! 20. Rxf2 Bxb5 { Black's pawn structute is significantly better }) (7. Qb3 Bb7 8. Bg2 a6 9. a4! (9. O-O c5 10. dxc5 Nbd7! $13 { Common idea not to rush with the capture on c5 }) 9... c5! 10. axb5 c4! 11. Qd1 axb5 { It's easier to play with the black pieces here }) 7... Bb7 8. Bg2 Nbd7 9. O-O c5 10. a4 b4 11. Bg5 Be7 12. Nbd2 Rc8 $15 13. Qd3 O-O 14. Rfc1 h6 15. Bxf6 Bxf6 16. e3 Rc7 $140 *


