1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 c6 4. e3 Nf6 5. Nf3 Nbd7 6. Bd3 (6. c5? { White is clearly not ready to take out the space on the queenside since the pressure in the center of the board is gone and black can attack the center and the c5 pawn } 6... b6! 7. b4 (7. cxb6 axb6 8. Bd3 Bd6 9. O-O O-O 10. e4 dxe4 11. Nxe4 Nxe4 12. Bxe4 Bb7 13. Bg5 Qc7 14. Re1 h6 15. Bh4 Nf6! $15) 7... a5 8. bxa5 (8. b5 Bb7! (8... cxb5? 9. c6 Nb8 10. Bxb5 $16) 9. cxb6 Bb4 10. Bd2 O-O 11. bxc6 Bxc6 12. Bd3 Nxb6 13. Ne5 Bb7 14. O-O Nc4!) 8... bxc5 $19) (6. Bd2 Bd6 7. Bd3 (7. Rc1 O-O 8. Bd3 dxc4 9. Bxc4 e5!? 10. O-O h6 { This prophylactic move may be very helpful to avoid the Ng5 move } 11. Qc2 Re8 12. Rfd1 e4 13. Ne1 Ng4 14. h3 Qh4 15. hxg4 Nf6! $19) (7. c5 Bc7 8. b4 e5! { It is very important to struck in the center with e5 } 9. Be2 e4 10. Ng1 h5 $40) (7. cxd5?! exd5 8. Bd3 O-O 9. O-O Re8 10. Qc2 Qe7 $15 { Black is taking over the e4 }) (7. Qc2 { transposition }) 7... O-O 8. O-O dxc4 9. Bxc4 b5 10. Bd3 b4 11. Ne4 (11. Na4 c5 12. dxc5 Nxc5 13. Nxc5 Bxc5 14. Qe2 Qd6! 15. Rfd1 Bb7 16. e4 Rfd8 17. Bg5 h6! 18. e5 Qc7 19. Bxf6 gxf6 20. exf6 Qf4 $36) 11... Nxe4 12. Bxe4 Bb7 13. Qc2 (13. Rc1 Rc8 14. Qa4 f5! 15. Bxc6?! (15. Bd3 c5 16. Qxa7?? { If the queen takes a poisoned pawn white is going to be facing a deadly mating attack } 16... Bxf3 17. gxf3 Qg5+ 18. Kh1 Qh5 $19) 15... Nb6 16. Bxb7 Rxc1 17. Qb3 Rxf1+ 18. Kxf1 Qe7 $15) 13... f5! 14. Bd3 c5 $15) (6. a3 Bd6 7. c5 (7. Bd3 O-O 8. O-O Re8 9. e4 (9. b4? e5! 10. dxe5 Nxe5 11. Nxe5 Bxe5 12. Bb2 Bxh2+! { white overlooked a nice combination } 13. Kxh2 Ng4+ 14. Kg1 Qh4 $19) (9. Qc2 e5 10. cxd5 cxd5 11. dxe5 (11. e4 exd4 12. Nxd5 Nxd5 13. exd5 h6 14. Nxd4 Qh4 15. Nf3 Qh5 $15) 11... Nxe5 12. Nxe5 Bxe5 13. h3 Be6 $36) 9... dxe4 10. Nxe4 Nxe4 11. Bxe4 e5! { Most of the time in such positions black plays Nf6 immediately but here we need the knight on d7 to be able to play e5 } 12. Re1 exd4 13. Qxd4 Bc5 14. Qd3 Nf6 15. Bg5 Qxd3 16. Bxd3 Rxe1+ 17. Rxe1 Be6 { with some chances for an initiative }) 7... Bc7 8. b4 e5 $15) (6. cxd5 exd5 { black has no issues here } 7. Bd3 (7. Be2 { too passive } 7... Bd6 8. O-O O-O 9. a3 Re8 10. b4 Nb6! 11. Qb3 Ne4 12. Nxe4 dxe4 13. Nd2 Be6 14. Qc2 Bf5 15. Qb3 Nd5 $40) 7... Bd6 8. O-O O-O 9. Qc2 (9. e4 dxe4 10. Nxe4 Nxe4 11. Bxe4 Re8 12. Bc2 h6 { avoiding the pin } 13. Qd3 Nf6 14. h3 Be6 15. Re1 Qb6 { keeping the dark-squared bishop tied to the b2 pawn } 16. Ne5 Rad8 $15) (9. b3 Re8 10. Bb2 Ne4 11. Qc2 Qe7 12. Rae1 h5!? (12... Ndf6 { might not be good due to the lack of defence around the e5 square } 13. Ne5!) 13. Ne2 h4 14. h3 a5 15. a3 Qf6 $15 { Black is dominating }) 9... Re8 10. Re1 Nf8!? 11. h3 (11. e4 dxe4 12. Nxe4 Nxe4 13. Bxe4 Be6 14. Bd2 Bc7 15. h3 Bd5 { black is doing great by controlling the center with a bishop and blocking the isolated pawn }) 11... Be6 12. Ng5 h6 13. Nxe6 Nxe6 14. Bd2 Ng5 15. Re2 Bc7 16. f4 Nge4 17. Be1 Qd6 18. b4 a6 19. Rc1 g5! $40 { 0-1 Hummel,P (2157)-Van den Doel,E (2560) Amsterdam op 2nd 2024 (3) }) (6. b3 Bb4!? { forcing the white bishop to the bad diagonal } 7. Bd2 (7. Bb2? { This move gets played quite often on a lower level } 7... Qa5! 8. Qc2 Ne4 9. Rc1 Qxa2 10. Bd3 Bxc3+ 11. Bxc3 Qxc2 12. Rxc2 Nxc3 13. Rxc3 dxc4 14. bxc4 b6 15. Ke2 Bb7 16. Rb1 c5 { white doesn't have any counterplay for the pawn }) 7... Qe7 8. Bd3 (8. Be2 O-O 9. O-O b6 10. Qc1 (10. Qc2 Bb7 11. Rad1 (11. Rfd1 Rac8 12. a3 Bd6 13. e4 dxe4 14. Nxe4 Nxe4 15. Qxe4 f5!? 16. Qe3 c5 $36 { The black bishops are targetting the kingside }) 11... Rac8 12. Qb2 Bd6 13. h3 dxc4?! (13... c5! { black is positionally better }) 14. bxc4 { 0-1 Mirzoev,A (2417)-Samunenkov,I (2515) Budapest FS08 GM 2023 (5) } (14. e4!)) (10. Ne5!? Bb7 11. Nxd7 Nxd7 12. Bd3 Nf6 13. Ne2 Bd6 14. Ng3 g6 15. Qe2 Rfe8 16. Rad1 Rad8 17. Bc3 e5 $15 { 0-1 Neverov,V (2438)-Li,D (2563) Prague op 2024 (5) }) 10... Bb7 11. a3 Bd6 $15 { 0-1 Djordjevic,V (2373)-Kramnik,V (2753) Speed Chess Q1 Sw Chess.com INT blitz 2023 (6) bishop on d2 is obviously misplaced }) 8... e5! (8... O-O!? 9. O-O h6 10. Qe2 dxc4 11. Bxc4 (11. bxc4 $146 e5! 12. Bc2 Re8 13. Rfe1 a5 14. a3 Bd6 15. h3 b6 16. Ne4 Nxe4 17. Bxe4 Bb7) 11... b5 { not the strongest continuation } (11... Rd8 12. Rad1 a5 13. Rfe1 e5 14. dxe5 Nxe5 15. Nxe5 Qxe5 16. Na4 Bd6) 12. Bd3 a6 13. a4 Bb7 14. Rac1 Rac8 15. e4 bxa4 16. e5 Nd5 17. Nxa4 Bxd2 18. Qxd2 c5 $15 { 0-1 Arabidze,M (2441)-Kramnik,V (2753) Titled Tuesday intern op 23rd May Late Chess.com INT blitz 2023 (2) and Kramnik takes over the initiative }) 9. dxe5 (9. Bc2 e4! 10. Ng1 Nf8 11. Nge2 Ng6 $40 { 0-1 Abbasov,F (2509)-Van Wely,L (2674) Baku President's Cup 2nd 2007 (8) }) 9... Nxe5 10. Nxe5 Qxe5 11. Rc1 dxc4 12. Bxc4 Bf5 $36) (6. Be2 { Interesting approach, the idea is to not rush with the capture on c4 } 6... Bd6 (6... dxc4!? 7. a4! (7. Bxc4 { transposition }) 7... Bd6 8. Nd2 O-O 9. Nxc4 Bc7 10. b3) 7. O-O (7. Qc2 { transposition }) (7. b3 O-O 8. O-O b6 9. Bb2 (9. a4) 9... Bb7 10. Qc2 Qe7 11. Rad1 Rad8 12. Rfe1 (12. e4 Nxe4 13. Nxe4 dxe4 14. Qxe4 f5!? 15. Qc2 (15. Qh4!? Qxh4 16. Nxh4 Rfe8 17. Nf3 c5 { black completely equalized }) 15... c5 16. Rfe1 Be4 17. Qc1 cxd4 18. Nxd4 Bc5 $15) 12... Rfe8 13. Bf1 e5 (13... c5!? { certainly worth consideration } 14. cxd5 exd5 15. g3 (15. Qf5 a6 16. g3 c4! 17. bxc4 dxc4 18. Bxc4? (18. e4 g6 19. Qh3 b5 $36 { white center is very vulnerable }) 18... g6 $19) 15... Rc8 16. Bh3 (16. Qb1 c4! 17. bxc4 Bb4 18. Nd2 dxc4 19. e4 Bxc3 20. Bxc3 Nxe4 21. Bb4 Nxd2 22. Rxe7 Nxb1 23. Rxd7 Be4 24. f3 Bg6 25. Rxa7 c3 26. d5 c2 27. Rc1 Nc3 28. d6 Ne2+ 29. Bxe2 Rxe2 30. d7 Rd8 31. Rc7 Bf5) (16. dxc5 Bxc5! 17. Qd3 Bb4 18. a3 Bxc3 19. Bxc3 Nc5 20. Qb1 Ng4! 21. Bd4 Ne4 { with a good play }) (16. Bg2 cxd4 17. Nxd4 (17. exd4 Ne4 18. Nd2 Ndf6 19. Ndxe4 (19. f3? Nxc3! 20. Rxe7 Ne2+ $19) 19... dxe4 20. d5 Bb4 { The pressure on the white's knight is extremely unpleasent }) 17... Bb4 18. Rc1 Ne4 19. Qd3? Ndc5? { 0-1 Gurevich,D (2396)-Drygalov,A (2501) Titled Tuesday intern op 22nd Nov Late Chess.com INT blitz 2022 (4) } (19... Ne5! $19)) 16... cxd4 17. Nxd4 (17. exd4 Ne4 18. Qd3 Qd8 19. Bf5 Nxc3 20. Rxe8+ Qxe8 21. Bxc3 g6 22. Re1 Qd8 23. Bh3 Rc7 24. Bd2 Nf6! 25. Bg5 Bb4 26. Rc1 Rxc1+ 27. Bxc1 Ne4 { the position is equal }) 17... Bb4 18. Bg2 (18. f3 a6 19. Rc1 g6 { blocking the f5 to prevent the knight's invasion }) 18... Ne4! $17 { 0-1 Laurusas,T (2571)-Esipenko,A (2680) EU-ch 23rd Vrnjacka Banja 2023 (8) }) 14. dxe5 Nxe5 15. Nxe5 (15. Nd4 dxc4 16. Nf5 Qe6 17. Nxd6 Rxd6 18. Rxd6 Qxd6 19. Rd1 cxb3 20. axb3 Qe7 21. Ne4 Nd5 22. Ng3 Bc8 23. e4 Nb4 24. Qc3 f6 25. h3 c5 26. f4 Nec6 $15 { 1/2 Giri,A (2745)-Erigaisi,A (2762) Warsaw Superbet Blitz 2024 (1) }) 15... Bxe5 16. cxd5 cxd5 17. Nb5 Rc8 18. Qb1 d4! { activating the light-squared bishop } 19. h3 Ng4 20. hxg4 Qh4 21. f4 dxe3 22. Rxe3 Bxf4 23. Rh3 Qxh3 24. gxh3 Be3+ 25. Kh2 Bf4+ 26. Kg1 { 1/2 Wang,H (2698)-Ding,L (2781) Danzhou 08th 2017 (1) }) 7... O-O 8. b3 Ne4! { black is reaching a favourable Stonewall set-up } 9. Bb2 f5 10. Bd3 Qf6 11. Ne2 g5 12. Rc1 a5 13. a4 h5?! (13... g4!? 14. Ne1 Qh6 $36) 14. Rc2 Rf7 15. Qa1 Qh6 16. Rd1 h4 $40 { 0-1 Nihal,S (2692)-Praggnanandhaa,R (2741) Che Thiruvananthapuram m blitz 2023 (1) }) 6... dxc4 7. Bxc4 b5 8. Bd3 (8. Be2 Bb7 9. O-O (9. e4 b4 10. e5 bxc3 11. exf6 Nxf6 (11... cxb2!? 12. fxg7 bxa1=Q 13. gxh8=Q $40) 12. bxc3 Bd6 13. O-O O-O 14. Bg5 c5 15. dxc5 Bxc5 { 0-1 Werle,J (2552)-Van Wely,L (2680) Staunton Memorial 5th London 2007 (4) }) (9. a3 a5!? 10. O-O Be7 { transposes to 9.0-0 }) 9... Be7 10. e4 (10. a3 a5! 11. b3 (11. Qc2 O-O 12. Rd1 Qb8! 13. e4 b4 14. Na4 c5 15. e5 Be4 16. Bd3 Bxd3 17. Qxd3 Nd5 $15) 11... O-O 12. Bb2 b4 13. axb4 axb4 14. Na4 c5 { black has equalized }) 10... b4 11. e5 bxc3 12. exf6 Bxf6 13. bxc3 c5 14. dxc5 O-O 15. Ba3 Be7! 16. Qd4 Qc7) (8. Bb3 { Black has no issues here at all } 8... b4! 9. Ne2 (9. Na4 { White is trying to fight for c5 } 9... Ba6! { preventing the short castle } 10. Bd2 Be7 11. Rc1 O-O 12. Bc4 (12. Rxc6? Bb5 13. Rc1 Rc8 $17 {