2 { White wants to place the rook on c1 as soon as possible } 12... Bd6 (12... Be7 13. Rac1 O-O 14. e4 Qb6 15. e5! $36 { 1-0 Jobava,B (2603)-Pichot,A (2630) Titled Tuesday intern op 13th Apr Chess.com INT blitz 2021 (9) }) 13. Rac1 Qb8 14. h3 O-O 15. Ng5 h6 16. Nge4 b4 17. Nxf6+ Nxf6 18. Na4 cxd4 19. exd4 Bd5 { Black is standing well. }) 12... cxd4 13. Nxd4 Bd6 { 0-1 Dardha,D (2449)-Guliyev,N (2529) Chartres Blitz Europe Echecs INT 2020 (14) } 14. g3 Qb8!? { The idea is to liberate the c8 square for the kingside rook } 15. Be3 O-O 16. Rac1 Ne5 17. Bb1 Rd8 18. Bg5 h6 19. Bxf6 gxf6 $15) (10. a4 b4 11. Ne4 (11. Nb1 c5 12. Nbd2 Be7 13. Qe2 (13. a5 O-O 14. Nc4 Qc7 15. h3 Rac8 16. Qe2 Be4 { good resource to get rid of the light-squared white bishop } 17. b3 Bxd3 18. Qxd3 cxd4 19. exd4 Rfd8 20. Qe2 Qb7 $15) 13... O-O 14. Rd1 (14. a5 Qc7 15. Rd1 Rfd8 16. Nc4 Be4!? 17. Bxe4 Nxe4 18. Bd2 Rac8 19. Rac1 Qb7 { Black is doing perfectly fine }) 14... cxd4 15. exd4 a5! { preventing a5 from white } 16. Bb5 h6) 11... c5 12. Nxf6+ (12. Ned2 Be7 { transposes to 11.Nb1 }) 12... Qxf6! { Creating some pressure on the white knight } 13. e4 cxd4 14. Bg5 Qg6 15. Rc1 Bc5 $13) 10... c5 11. d5 (11. e5 cxd4 12. Nxb5 (12. exf6? dxc3 13. fxg7 Bxg7 $19) 12... Bxf3! 13. Qxf3 Nd5 14. Nxd4 Nxe5 15. Qe4 Nxd3 16. Qxd3 Bc5 17. Nf3 O-O 18. Bd2 Qb6 { 0-1 Piket,J (2570)-Kramnik,V (2775) Amber-blindfold 05th Monte Carlo rapid 1996 (4) }) 11... Qc7 12. dxe6 (12. Bc2 O-O-O 13. dxe6 Ne5! 14. Qe2 Nxf3+ 15. Qxf3 fxe6 16. Bf4 Bd6 17. Bxd6 Qxd6 { Black's position is excellent and they are ready to start a kingside attack }) (12. Qe2 c4 { 1/2 Giri,A (2764)-Erigaisi,A (2722) Tata Steel-A 85th Wijk aan Zee 2023 (6) } 13. Bc2 Bd6 14. Bg5 (14. dxe6 fxe6 15. Nd4 (15. Ng5 Nc5 16. f4 h6 17. Nf3 (17. e5!? hxg5 18. exd6 Qxd6 19. Bg6+ Ke7 $17 { King is completely safe in the center }) (17. Nh3 Nd3! 18. e5 Bc5+ 19. Kh1 Nd5 20. Ne4 O-O-O $17) 17... Nd3! { the only move } 18. Bxd3 cxd3 19. Qxd3 O-O 20. e5 Bc5+ 21. Kh1 Nd5 $17 { Black's dynamic play fully justifies the pawn sacrifice. }) (15. Re1 Ne5! { taking over the e5 } 16. Ng5 Qe7 17. f4 Bc5+ 18. Kh1 Nd3 19. Bxd3 cxd3 20. Qxd3 Ng4 21. Rf1 O-O! (21... Nf2+?? 22. Rxf2 Bxf2 23. Qh3! $13)) 15... Bxh2+!? 16. Kh1 Nc5 17. f4 e5! 18. Ndxb5 (18. Nd5! Nxd5 19. exd5 O-O $13) 18... axb5 19. Kxh2 h5 20. Nxb5 Ng4+ 21. Kg3 Qd7 $40) 14... O-O-O 15. dxe6 fxe6 16. Rad1 h6 17. Bh4 g5! 18. Bg3 Bxg3 19. hxg3 Kb8 20. Rd2 g4 21. Nh4 b4 22. Na4 Ne5 { Black has full control of the center }) 12... fxe6 13. Bc2 (13. Ng5 Qc6! 14. Qe2 (14. Be2 b4! 15. Na4 h6 16. Bh5+ (16. Nh3 Rd8 17. Bh5+ Ke7 18. Be3 g5! $15) 16... g6! 17. Bxg6+ Ke7 $17) (14. f4 h6 15. Nf3 O-O-O $36) 14... c4 15. Bc2 Bc5 16. b4 (16. Be3 O-O 17. Rad1 Rae8 18. h3 Ne5 19. f4 Nd3 20. Bxd3 cxd3 21. Qxd3 h6 22. Nf3 Rd8 $36) 16... Bd4 17. Bb2 e5 18. Nf3 Qd6 19. a3 Nh5) (13. e5 { White doesn't have enough counterplay to balance the material loss. } 13... Nxe5 14. Nxe5 Qxe5 15. Re1 Qd6 16. Qe2 O-O-O 17. Bc2 Qc7! $40 { preparing Bd6 }) 13... Bd6 14. Ng5 Nf8! 15. f4 O-O-O 16. Qe2 (16. Qe1 e5 17. Nd5 (17. f5 h6 18. Nf3 N8d7 $15) 17... Bxd5 18. exd5 exf4 19. Bd2 Re8! 20. Qf2 h6 21. Ne6 Nxe6 22. dxe6 Kb8 $13 { Both sides have chances for a counterplay }) (16. a4 b4 17. Qe2 h6 18. Nf3 Bxf4 19. e5 Bxf3 20. Rxf3 Bxe5 21. Qxa6+ Kb8 22. Rxf6 gxf6 23. Be4 Qa7 24. Qb5+ Kc8 25. Be3 bxc3 26. bxc3 Bd6 { 0-1 Laznicka,V (2683)-Shirov,A (2706) Novy Bor m 2012 (4) }) 16... h6 17. Nf3 (17. Nh3 e5 18. f5 c4 19. Be3 Bc5 $17) 17... Bxf4 18. e5 (18. Bxf4 Qxf4 19. g3 (19. Rae1 Ng4 20. g3 Qb8 21. e5 Bxf3 22. Qxf3 Nxe5 23. Rxe5 Qxe5 24. Qa8+ Qb8 25. Qc6+ Qc7) 19... Qg4 20. e5 Nd5 21. Ne4 Nf4! (21... Nd7?! 22. Nd6+ Kb8 23. Nxb7 Kxb7 24. Be4 $13 { 0-1 Vera Gonzalez Quevedo,R (2437)-Dreev,A (2644) Carlos Torre Memorial op 27th Merida 2015 (5) }) 22. Qe3 Nh3+ 23. Kh1 Rd5 24. Nf2 Nxf2+ 25. Rxf2 Qd4!! 26. Nxd4 Rxe5+ 27. Be4 Rxe4 28. Qxe4 Bxe4+ 29. Nf3 Nd7 30. Kg1 Kc7 31. Re1 Bd5 { 0-1 Rubinas,P (2574)-Mueller,G (2568) SUI 25 Jubilee/A ema