1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 c6 4. e3 Nf6 5. Nf3 Nbd7 { White doesn't mind to wait a little bit } 6. Qc2 Bd6 (6... b6!? { black wants to avoid 7.g4 } 7. Bd3 (7. Be2 Bb7 8. O-O Bd6 9. e4 dxe4 10. Nxe4 Nxe4 11. Qxe4 Nf6 12. Qh4 c5 13. Rd1 Qc7 14. Be3 h6 { 0-1 Duda,J (2750)-Carlsen,M (2864) Charity Cup KO chess24.com INT rapid 2022 (3.12) The position remains dynamic, offering good prospects for both players. }) (7. cxd5 cxd5 8. Nb5 (8. Bd3 Bb7 9. O-O a6 10. a4 Bd6 11. Bd2 O-O 12. Rac1 Qe7 13. Qb1 Rfc8 14. Rfd1 h6 { 1/2 Khusenkhojaev,M (2410)-Dreev,A (2662) St Petersburg Summer rapid 2014 (3) }) 8... Bb4+ 9. Bd2 Bxd2+ 10. Nxd2 O-O { 0-1 Khismatullin,D (2579)-Carlsen,M (2830) Wch Rapid Samarkand 2023 (2) } 11. Be2 Ba6 { white is probably slightly better }) (7. b3 Bb7 8. Bb2 Bd6 9. Bd3 O-O 10. O-O Re8 11. Rad1 c5 12. cxd5 exd5 $13) 7... Bb7 8. O-O Be7 9. b3 (9. Rd1 dxc4!? 10. Bxc4 c5 11. e4 cxd4 12. Nxd4 O-O 13. Bxe6 fxe6 14. Nxe6 Qe8 15. Nxf8 Nxf8 16. f3 Bc5+! 17. Kh1 Ne6 $13 { with dynamic play }) (9. e4 dxe4 10. Nxe4 c5 { Black should be able to fully equalize shortly }) 9... O-O 10. Bb2 h6 11. Rad1 { white is preparing e4 } 11... Qc7 12. Qe2 (12. e4 dxe4 13. Nxe4 Nxe4 14. Bxe4 Nf6 15. Bd3 c5) (12. Rfe1 Rad8 13. h3 Qb8 14. e4 dxe4 15. Nxe4 c5 16. Nxf6+ Bxf6 (16... Nxf6?? 17. d5! $18)) 12... Rad8 13. Bb1 c5 14. cxd5 Nxd5 (14... exd5?! 15. Nh4! $36) 15. Nxd5 Bxd5 16. Rc1 Qb8 17. Rfd1 Bxf3 18. Qxf3 cxd4 19. Bxd4 Bf6) 7. Bd3 (7. cxd5 { Exchanges are in Black’s favor. } 7... exd5 8. Bd3 O-O 9. O-O (9. g4? { White is trying to surprise black with a kingside attack } 9... g6! 10. g5 Nh5 $17) 9... Re8 10. Re1 (10. e4 dxe4 11. Nxe4 Nxe4 12. Bxe4 Nf6 13. Bg5 h6! $15) 10... Nf8! 11. h3 Be6 12. Bd2 h6 13. Ne5 c5 14. f4 a6 { Interesting position with plenty of strategic opportunities. }) (7. e4 { too early } 7... dxe4 8. Nxe4 Nxe4 9. Qxe4 e5! 10. dxe5 O-O 11. exd6 Re8 12. Qxe8+ Qxe8+ 13. Be3 Ne5 14. Nxe5 Qxe5 15. O-O-O Be6 $17 { 0-1 Szeberenyi,A (2349)-Dragnev,V (2551) HUN-chT 2223 Hungary 2022 (9.7) }) (7. Bd2 { white wants to avoid the capture on c4 by temporarely keeping the bishop on f1 } 7... O-O 8. Rd1 (8. e4 e5!? { 0-1 Vaisser,A (2548)-Sjugirov,S (2646) Moscow Aeroflot rapid op qual 2013 (3) } 9. O-O-O exd4 10. Nxd4 Nxe4 11. Nxe4 dxe4 12. Qxe4 Re8 13. Qc2 Nc5 $40) (8. h3 { Grandmaster Meskovs played it several times. White is setting up for a kingside attack } 8... b6 9. g4 dxc4! 10. g5 (10. Bxc4 Bb7 $17) 10... Nd5 11. Bxc4 Bb7 12. O-O-O Rc8 13. Kb1 b5! 14. Bd3 c5 $40) (8. Bd3 dxc4 9. Bxc4 b5 10. Bd3 Bb7 11. O-O (11. e4 e5 12. dxe5 Nxe5 13. Nxe5 Bxe5 14. f4 Bd4 15. e5 Ng4 16. Bxh7+ Kh8 17. O-O-O Nf2 $15) (11. Ng5 { White wants to control c5 by rerouting the knight } 11... h6 12. Nge4 Be7 13. Nxf6+ Nxf6 14. Ne4 c5! 15. dxc5 Nxe4 16. Bxe4 Bxe4 17. Qxe4 Bxc5) 11... b4! 12. Ne4 Nxe4 13. Bxe4 Nf6?! { 1/2 Karpov,A (2745)-Gelfand,B (2695) Biel Credit Suisse 1997 (7) Gelfand didn't find the best continuation } (13... f5! 14. Bd3 c5 $17)) (8. O-O-O e5!? (8... b5 9. cxb5 Bb7 $44) 9. cxd5 cxd5 10. Nb5 Bb8 11. dxe5 Nxe5 12. Bc3 (12. Nxe5 Bxe5 13. Bc3 Qe7 14. Kb1 Bd7 15. Bxe5 Qxe5 16. Nd4 Rac8 17. Qd2 Ba4 $40) 12... a6! 13. Nbd4 Ne4 14. Nxe5 Bxe5 $15) 8... Qe7 9. Be2 (9. a3 a6!? 10. Bd3 (10. b4 e5! $32) 10... dxc4 11. Bxc4 b5 12. Bd3 c5 { black has better chances to gain the advantage }) 9... dxc4 10. Bxc4 e5 { quiet a typical idea for Anti-Meran system } 11. dxe5 Nxe5 12. Nxe5 Qxe5 $15 { white dark-squared bishop is clearly missplaced and black is aiming to take over the initiative }) (7. g4 h6 { Solid approach } 8. Rg1 (8. Bd2 dxc4 9. Bxc4 b5 10. Be2 Bb7 11. e4 (11. Rg1 Rc8 12. a3 c5! 13. Nxb5 Bb8 14. Qa4 Ne4 $15) 11... Be7 12. e5 b4! { not allowing the white knight to e4 } 13. exf6 (13. Na4 Nd5 14. O-O c5!? 15. Nxc5 Nxc5 16. dxc5 O-O $36) 13... bxc3 14. fxe7 cxd2+ 15. Qxd2 Qxe7 16. O-O O-O 17. Rac1 c5 { The position is more favourable for the black side }) (8. h3 e5! 9. Bd2 O-O 10. dxe5 Nxe5 11. Nxe5 Bxe5 { 0-1 Jakovenko,D (2736)-Gelfand,B (2758) FIDE World Cup Khanty-Mansiysk 2009 (5.5) } 12. O-O-O Qe7 13. Kb1 dxc4 14. Bxc4 b5 15. Bd3 c5 $13) 8... e5 9. cxd5 (9. h4 exd4 10. Nxd4?! (10. exd4 dxc4 11. g5 (11. Bxc4 Nb6 12. Be2 Be6 13. g5 Nfd5! 14. gxh6 gxh6 15. Ne4 Nb4 16. Qb1 Qe7 $15) 11... Nd5 12. Bxc4 N7b6 13. gxh6 gxh6 14. Bxd5 Nxd5 15. Nxd5 cxd5 16. Be3 Be6 17. Qb3 Qf6 18. Ne5 O-O-O! $15) 10... Ne5! 11. g5 hxg5 12. hxg5 Nfg4 13. cxd5 c5! $17 14. Qe4 cxd4 15. exd4 f5 16. Qe2 O-O! 17. dxe5 Bxe5 18. Be3 f4 19. Rxg4 fxe3 20. fxe3 Qb6! 21. O-O-O Bxg4 22. Qxg4 Qxe3+ $17) 9... cxd5 10. Nb5 Bb8 11. g5 (11. Bd2 e4! 12. Nh4 Nb6 13. h3 Nh7! 14. Nf5 g6 15. Ng3 Ng5 $19) 11... hxg5 12. Nxg5 e4 13. Bd2 Nb6 { black wants to get rid of the white knight on b5 and then target the h2 pawn } 14. Rc1 (14. Qc5 Bd7 15. Rc1 { transposition }) (14. h3 a6 15. Ba5! Bf5! 16. Nc3 Bh2 17. Rg2 Bc7 18. Qb3 Rc8 19. Rg1 g6 20. a4 Nc4 $40 { 0-1 Houska,J (2467)-Efremov,A (2574) ICCF GMN/026 email ICCF email 2011 }) 14... Bd7 15. Bb4 (15. Qc5 Bc6! 16. Ba5 Nfd7 17. Nd6+ Bxd6 18. Qxd6 Nc4! 19. Bxd8 Nxd6 20. Bc7 Nf5 $15) (15. Nc7+ Bxc7 16. Qxc7 Qxc7 17. Rxc7 Rc8! 18. Rxb7 Rc2 19. Bb4 Nc8 20. Bd2 Rxh2 21. Rb8 Rc6 22. Bb5 Rc7 23. Be2 Ng8 $36) 15... Bc6 16. Qc5 (16. f4 Ng8! $146 17. a4 a6 18. Nc3 Bd6 19. Ba5 Bc7 $15) 16... Nc8 17. Bh3 Ne7 18. Nd6+ Bxd6 19. Qxd6 Qxd6 20. Bxd6 Nfg8!! 21. Bc5 Rh4 22. Rg4 Rh5 $17) 7... O-O 8. O-O dxc4 9. Bxc4 a6!? { profilactic move, the idea is to prepare b5 and c5, Bb7 } 10. Rd1 (10. a4 c5 11. dxc5 (11. Rd1 cxd4 12. exd4 (12. Nxd4? { missing a double threat } 12... Qc7! $15) (12. Ne4 Nxe4 13. Qxe4 e5 14. exd4 Nf6 15. Qe2 e4 16. Ne5 Bf5 17. Bg5 h6 18. Bh4 Qc7! 19. Bxf6 gxf6 20. Ng4 Kg7 21. g3 Bg6 { Black has a strong position, ready to activate the bishops and press for an advantage }) 12... Qc7 13. Qe2 b6 14. Bg5 (14. d5 Ne5 15. Nxe5 Bxe5 16. dxe6 Bxe6 17. Bxe6 fxe6 18. h3 Rfe8 19. Be3 Bxc3 20. bxc3 Nd5 { 0-1 Bok,B (2587)-Vidit,S (2720) Crunchlab PlayIn Match D2 Chess.com INT rapid 2024 (1.1) }) (14. h3 Bb7 15. d5 exd5 16. Nxd5 Nxd5 17. Bxd5 Bxd5 18. Rxd5 Nf6) 14... h6 15. Bxf6 Nxf6 16. Rac1 Bb7 17. d5 exd5 18. Nxd5 Nxd5 19. Bxd5 Bc5 20. Qe5 { 1/2 Finegold,B (2513)-Robson,R (2491) Lubbock SPICE Cup-B 2009 (4) }) 11... Bxc5 12. b3 b6 13. Ne4 (13. Bb2 Bb7 14. Rad1 Qe7) 13... Be7 14. Rd1 Bb7 15. Nxf6+ Bxf6 16. Nd4 Qb8 17. Ba3 Nc5 18. a5 Rc8 19. axb6 Be4 20. Qe2 Qxb6 { 1/2 Galanov,S (2585)-Zhak,B (2653) RCCA Diamond email ICCF email 2010 }) (10. e4 e5 11. Rd1 (11. h3 b5! 12. Be2 Re8 { aiming for the e4 pawn } 13. Be3 Qc7 14. Rad1 exd4 15. Nxd4 b4! 16. Na4 c5 17. Nf5 Bh2+ 18. Kh1 Nxe4 19. g3 Ndf6! 20. Nh6+ gxh6 21. Kxh2 Bb7 { 1/2 Acevedo Villalba,A (2553)-Wilczek,T (2606) W-ch31 q06 email ICCF email 2011 }) 11... Qc7 12. h3 b5 13. Bb3 Bb7 14. dxe5 Nxe5 15. Nd4 (15. Nh4 c5 16. Nf5 Rfd8 17. Bg5 c4 18. Bxf6 gxf6 19. Qc1 Bf8 20. Bc2 Rxd1+ 21. Qxd1 Ng6 22. Qf3 Rd8 23. Rd1 Rxd1+ 24. Qxd1 Bc5 25. b3 { 1/2 Saidashev,A (2450)-Fuller,W (2403) Champion's League 2021/B4 email ICCF email }) 15... Rfd8 { Liberating the f8 for the dark-squared bishop } 16. Bg5 c5 17. Nf5 c4 { transposition }) (10. Bd3 c5! { There’s no need to push b5 } 11. Bd2 (11. Rd1 Qc7 12. h3 cxd4 13. exd4 b5 14. Ne4 Qxc2 15. Bxc2 Be7 { Black should be fine playing the endgame against the IQP })) 10... b5 11. Bd3 (11. Be2 Qc7 12. Ne4 (12. e4 e5 13. g3 (13. dxe5 Nxe5 14. Nxe5 Bxe5 15. g3 Re8 $15 { black should constantly target e4 }) 13... Re8 14. a3 exd4 15. Nxd4 Be5 16. Bf3 c5 { 1/2 Mamedyarov,S (2764)-Carlsen,M (2882) Sinquefield Cup 7th Saint Louis 2019 (4) } 17. Nf5 g6 18. Nh6+ Kg7 19. Bg5 Bb7 20. Bg2 Bd4 { with a dynamic play }) 12... Nxe4 13. Qxe4 Bb7 14. Bd3 g6 15. Qh4 c5! 16. Ng5 h5 17. Ne4 (17. g4 Nf6! 18. gxh5 Nxh5 19. Be2 Kg7! $36) 17... Bxe4 { Trading off the knight will allow Black to neutralize the kingside pressure } 18. Bxe4 Rac8 19. Bd2 c4 20. f4 (20. Bc2 Kg7 21. a3 Nf6 $15) 20... b4 21. Rdc1 Nb6 22. Qe1 a5! $17) 11... Bb7 12. Ng5 h6 (12... Bxh2+? 13. Kxh2 Ng4+ 14. Kg1 Qxg5 15. f3 Ngf6 16. e4! $44) 13. Nge4 Bb8! { 0-1 Rahul,S (2494)-Antipov,M (2602) US Masters op Charlotte 2024 (4) } 14. b4 (14. a3 c5! 15. dxc5 Qc7 16. f4 Nxc5 17. Nxb5 axb5 18. Nxc5 Bc6 19. b4 e5! $36 { black pieces are getting activated }) 14... a5! { should be always considered after b4 } 15. bxa5 Qxa5 16. Bd2 Rc8 17. Nxf6+ (17. Nxb5 cxb5! 18. Nxf6+ gxf6 19. Qxc8+ Bxc8 20. Bxa5 Rxa5 21. Rdb1 Ba6 22. a4 bxa4 23. Bxa6 Rxa6 24. Rb7 Ra7 25. Rxa7 Bxa7 26. Rxa4 Bb6) 17... Nxf6 18. Ne4 Qc7 19. Nxf6+ gxf6 20. g3 c5 21. Bxb5 Qd6! 22. Qc4 Bf3 23. Re1 f5 $44 *


