1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 c6 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Nf3 (5. g3 { The bishop on g2 is going to be quite limited by the black pawns } 5... Nf6 6. Bg2 Bd6 7. Nf3 O-O { Essentially we received a reversed Caro-Kann } 8. O-O Re8 9. Qc2 { preventing the bishop from going to f5 } (9. a3 Bf5 10. b4 Nbd7 11. Nh4 Be6 12. b5 Rc8 $15) (9. Bg5 Nbd7 10. a3 h6 $15) (9. Re1 Bf5 10. Nh4 Be6 11. e4 dxe4 12. Nxe4 Nxe4 13. Bxe4 Nd7 $15) (9. Bf4 Bxf4! 10. gxf4 Ne4 11. Nxe4 (11. e3 Nd6 12. Kh1 Nd7) 11... Rxe4 12. e3 Re6 $140 13. Kh1 Rh6 $15) 9... Nbd7 10. Re1 h6 11. e4 dxe4 12. Nxe4 Nxe4 13. Rxe4 Rxe4 14. Qxe4 Nf6 { Black has nothing to worry about here }) (5. Qc2 { typical idea to prevent Bf5 } 5... Bd6 6. Nf3 h6!? (6... Ne7 { main move but it allows Bg5 } 7. Bg5 f6 8. Bh4 Bf5 9. Qd2 O-O 10. e3 Nd7 11. Bg3 Nb6 12. Nh4 Be6 13. Bd3 { white's chances are slightly better }) 7. g3 (7. Ne5 Nf6 8. Bf4 O-O 9. e3 Ng4 10. Nf3 Bxf4 11. exf4 c5! { creating pressure around d4 } 12. h3 cxd4 13. Nxd4 Nf6) (7. e4 dxe4 8. Nxe4 (8. Qxe4+ Ne7 9. Bc4 O-O 10. O-O Nd7 11. Re1 Nf6 12. Qe2 Re8 13. Qc2 Ned5 { Black has an edge }) 8... Nf6 9. Nxd6+ Qxd6 10. Be2 O-O 11. O-O Be6 12. Qc5 Rd8 13. Qxd6 Rxd6 14. Bf4 Rd8 15. Rfd1 Nbd7 16. a3 Bb3 17. Re1 Nf8 18. Rac1 Ne6 19. Be3 a5 20. Nd2 Ba2 21. Ra1 Bd5 { 0-1 Saydaliev,A (2213)-Yakubboev,N (2665) UZB-ch Tashkent rapid 2024 (21) }) (7. e3 Nf6 8. Bd3 O-O 9. O-O Re8 10. h3 Qe7 11. Re1 Ne4 $15) 7... Nf6 { transposition }) (5. Bf4 Bd6 6. Bxd6 (6. Bg3 Ne7 7. e3 Nf5! { black is planning to reroute the knight to d6 } 8. Bd3 (8. Bxd6 Nxd6 9. Bd3 Bf5 10. Bxf5 Nxf5 11. Qg4 g6 12. e4 dxe4 13. Qxe4+ Ne7 14. h4 O-O 15. h5 Nd5 16. Nge2 Re8 17. Qf3 Qf6 18. hxg6 fxg6 19. Qh3 Qf7 20. O-O-O Nd7 { 1/2 Andreikin,D (2736)-Harikrishna,P (2766) Tata Steel-A 79th Wijk aan Zee 2017 (7) }) 8... Nxg3 9. hxg3 Nd7 10. Qc2 Nf6 11. O-O-O { 0-1 Iturrizaga Bonelli,E (2621)-Postny,E (2577) EU-chT 24th Budva 2023 (2.6) } 11... h6! 12. Kb1 O-O { Black should not be afraid of the kingside attack } 13. f3 Re8! 14. e4 dxe4 15. fxe4 Ng4 $17) (6. Qd2 Nf6 7. Nf3 Ne4! $146 { This move wasn't played before but is certainly underestimated } 8. Nxe4 (8. Qc1 O-O 9. Bxd6 Nxd6 10. e3 Bf5 { It's a wonderful position for black, dark-squared bishops are exchanged and black has nothing to worry about }) 8... dxe4 9. Qe3 O-O! 10. Qxe4?? (10. Bxd6 Qxd6 11. Qxe4? (11. Nd2 f5 12. Qc3 Be6 13. e3 Nd7 14. Bc4 Bd5 { Black has more space in the center and ready to expand on the kingside }) 11... Qb4+! $17) 10... Re8 $19) 6... Qxd6 7. e3 Bf5 8. Bd3 (8. Qb3!? { Interesting move, it played by GM Sarana a few times } 8... Qe7 (8... Nd7!? 9. Qxb7 Rb8 10. Qxa7 Rxb2 11. Qa8+ Rb8 12. Qa4 Ngf6 13. Nf3 Rb4? (13... O-O! 14. Nh4 Be6 15. Bd3 Ne4 16. Nxe4 dxe4 17. Bxe4 f5 18. Bd3 Nc5 $13) 14. Qa8+ Rb8 15. Qa4 Rb4 16. Qa8+ Rb8 17. Qa4 Rb4 18. Qa8+ Rb8 19. Qa4 Rb4 20. Qa8+ Rb8 { 1/2 Baldauf,M (2506)-Doric,D (2457) Bundesliga 2223 Germany 2022 (13.1) }) 9. Nge2 (9. Nf3 Nf6 10. Nh4 (10. Be2 O-O 11. O-O Ne8! 12. Na4 Nd6 13. Nc5 Bg4 14. h3 Bxf3 15. Bxf3 Nd7 { 1/2 Seirawan,Y (2640)-Henrichs,T (2430) NED-chT 0001 playoff Breda 2001 (2.2) }) 10... Be6 11. Bd3 Ne4) 9... Nf6 10. Ng3 Bg6 11. h4 h6 12. Nce2!? O-O 13. Nf4 Bh7 14. Bd3 Bxd3 15. Qxd3 Nbd7 16. Nf5 Qb4+ 17. Qc3 a5 18. f3 h5 19. Nd3?! Qb6 20. O-O-O g6 21. Ng3 Rfe8 22. Rhe1 Qc7 23. Nf4 a4 24. Kb1 Re7?! { 1-0 Sarana,A (2662)-Tari,A (2672) Chess.com Rapid Wk25 Swiss Chess.com INT 2022 (5) } (24... a3 $36)) (8. Nf3 Qe7!? { preventing Nh4 } 9. Bd3 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 Nf6) (8. Nge2 Nd7 9. Ng3 Bg6 10. h4 h6 11. h5 Bh7 12. Bd3 Bxd3 13. Qxd3 Ne7! { Black has to cover f5 from the white knight } 14. O-O-O O-O 15. Kb1 b5 16. Rc1 Nb6 17. Nce2 a5 (17... Nc4! $36) 18. f3? Nc4 $17 { 0-1 Levtchouk,G (2300)-Lesiege,A (2460) Quebec-ch 1994 (5) }) 8... Bxd3 9. Qxd3 Nf6 10. Nf3 Nbd7 11. O-O O-O 12. b4) 5... Bf5 { It is crucial to control h7-b1 diagonal } 6. Bf4 (6. Bg5 Qb6! (6... Be7!? 7. Bxe7 Qxe7 8. e3 Nf6 9. Bd3 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 Nbd7 11. O-O O-O 12. Rab1 (12. Nd2 Rfe8 13. b4 a5! 14. b5 c5 { with a dynamic play }) (12. b4 Rfc8 13. a4 a5! 14. bxa5 (14. b5 c5 { Black's position is preferable }) 14... Rxa5 15. Rfb1 Ra7) 12... Ne4 13. b4 (13. Nd2 f5 14. b4 a6 15. a4 Nb6 $15) 13... a6 14. a4 Nb6! 15. a5 Nxc3 16. Qxc3 Nc4 17. Nd2 Nxd2 18. Qxd2 Rae8 $15 { White doesn't have any counterplay on the queenside }) 7. Qd2 (7. Qc1 Nd7 8. e3 Ngf6 9. Be2 Bd6 10. O-O O-O 11. Nh4 Be6 12. Nf3 Qc7 13. Bh4 Ne4 14. Qc2 f5 15. Bg3 Nxg3 16. hxg3 Nf6 17. Ng5 Qe7 18. Nxe6 Qxe6 19. Rab1 Rae8 $40 { 0-1 Ding,L (2654)-Zhou,J (2636) CHN-ch rap KO 1st Hefei rapid 2011 (2.2) }) 7... Nd7 8. e3 Ngf6 9. Bxf6 (9. a3 Bd6 10. Be2 O-O 11. O-O Ne4 12. Nxe4 dxe4 13. Ne1 Qc7 $15) (9. Bd3 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 Bd6 11. O-O O-O 12. Rab1 Rfe8) 9... Nxf6 10. a3 Bd6 11. Be2 O-O 12. O-O Qc7 13. h3 Qe7 $17 { Black is totally dominating with a pair of bishops and space advantage }) (6. Qb3 Qb6 7. Qxb6 (7. Bf4 Nd7 8. e3 Ngf6 9. Be2 Be7 10. O-O Qxb3 11. axb3 Ne4) 7... axb6 8. Bf4 Nd7 9. e3 Ngf6 10. Be2 b5 $15) (6. h3!? Bd6 7. Bg5 (7. g4 Bg6 8. Qb3 Nd7 9. Qxb7 Ne7 10. Qb3 Rb8 11. Qd1 Be4 12. Bg2 f5 $17) 7... Qb6 8. e4 Bxe4! 9. Nxe4 dxe4 10. Nd2 Qa5 11. Qg4 f5 12. Qh5+ g6 13. Qh4 h6 $15) 6... Bd6 7. Bg3 (7. Bxd6 Qxd6 8. e3 Nd7 9. Bd3 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 Ngf6 { transposition }) 7... Nf6 8. e3 O-O 9. Nh4 Bg4 10. Qc2 Bxg3 11. hxg3 Qd6 12. Bd3 Nbd7 13. O-O Rfe8 14. Rab1 g6 15. b4 Kg7 16. b5 c5 17. dxc5 Nxc5 18. Be2 Nce4 19. Bxg4 Nxg4 20. Ne2 Rac8 $36 *


